1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,800
I think we need to put you
in a wheelchair.

2
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:15,867
Will I be able to walk again?

3
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,733
Emma, don't take this
the wrong way okay?

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:20,567
But I need to remind you
that that child isn't ours.

5
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:23,167
This reminds me of when I needed
to bring Kyla to the hospital.

6
00:00:23,233 --> 00:00:25,400
I thought I'll be able to live
like a normal teenager,

7
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:26,300
why did this happen to me?

8
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:28,967
Why did they give me false hope?

9
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:30,900
Just when she's about
to enroll in school,

10
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:32,500
her legs got paralyzed.

11
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,700
I'm actually relieved
that it happened.

12
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,400
I want her to stay home

13
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:38,600
so I can keep an eye on her
at all times.

14
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:42,133
You sound like you wanted this
to happen to your daughter.

15
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:46,933
Flor, why do I feel like
I'm not getting better?

16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,133
Olive is insisting that
the child is not fit.

17
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,367
But when we ran some tests,

18
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:53,033
we didn't see anything
wrong with her.

19
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:55,233
In fact, she was
perfectly healthy.

20
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,200
Why do I feel like this, Danilo.

21
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:42,100
I know that Samantha
is not my child.

22
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:46,433
But why am I in so much pain?

23
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:52,200
Why is it so hard to let her go?

24
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:57,000
You know...

25
00:01:57,067 --> 00:01:58,333
It feels like...

26
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:03,367
I lost my child once again.

27
00:02:06,867 --> 00:02:10,867
This is why I don't want you
to take care of her.

28
00:02:10,933 --> 00:02:13,067
Because I know
you'll get attached.

29
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:17,667
And you'll have a hard time
letting her go.

30
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:24,467
I know, I said I'm done
grieving for Kyla,

31
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:26,333
that I've moved on.

32
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,200
But...

33
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:33,667
I haven't moved on yet.

34
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:37,833
I keep thinking about
what happened to her.

35
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:42,767
Danilo,

36
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:45,233
when will this pain end?

37
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:51,700
I see her everywhere.

38
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:55,067
I think of her everytime
I see children,

39
00:02:55,133 --> 00:03:00,100
I dream of her every night.

40
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:03,167
A lot of years have passed
but until now...

41
00:03:05,267 --> 00:03:07,700
I still can't forget
what happened to her.

42
00:03:10,767 --> 00:03:13,000
I didn't want you to know, Emma,

43
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,800
but even I...

44
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:20,100
until now...

45
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:21,933
I'm still in pain.

46
00:03:22,933 --> 00:03:25,467
I still can't believe that...

47
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:27,133
my baby daughter is gone.

48
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:31,267
It feels like
a big part of me...

49
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:34,267
died with her.

50
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:42,067
You know if only God
could grant me one wish,

51
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:48,567
I'll ask for our daughter back.

52
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:53,133
Even if I'll just see her once,

53
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,133
I will do anything...

54
00:03:58,733 --> 00:04:00,733
just to hear her voice.

55
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:31,100
- Hi, Mookie!
- Auntie!

56
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:32,900
- Hello!
- Hello, Auntie.

57
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:35,867
Where's your mom?

58
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:37,200
She's sleeping.

59
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:41,367
Actually, I just stopped by
to check up on you.

60
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:43,767
How are you feeling?
I heard what happened.

61
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:46,500
I'm fine.

62
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,433
I have something for you.

63
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,700
I have a gift
for you to cheer you up.

64
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,233
Thank you, Auntie.

65
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:02,100
You didn't like my gift?

66
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:05,667
Oh no, I do, Auntie.

67
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:08,033
Actually, I like it.

68
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,267
Thank you.

69
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:15,367
Is there something
bothering you, Mookie?

70
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:19,167
My mommy got mad at me
the other night.

71
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:21,333
Why? What happened?

72
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:25,967
I went to her office
to say goodnight.

73
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:29,067
Then I accidentally dropped
her stuff on the floor.

74
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:33,300
So I offered to help her.

75
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:37,733
But when I picked up
this one paper from an envelope.

76
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:39,933
She suddenly got mad at me.

77
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:42,633
Really?

78
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,833
Yes.

79
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:45,867
She yelled at me.

80
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,633
What was on the paper?

81
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,800
I didn't see much.

82
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:59,633
But I saw St. Agnes Children's
Hospital written on it.

83
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:06,000
That was a very strange case.

84
00:06:06,067 --> 00:06:07,133
Why?

85
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:11,800
Olive is insisting that
the child is unfit.

86
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,633
But when we ran some tests,

87
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,000
you know,

88
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:17,333
we didn't see anything
wrong with her.

89
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:20,600
In fact,
she was perfectly healthy.

90
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:24,667
And when we showed Olive
the result,

91
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:26,767
she was so angry.

92
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:30,633
She pulled Mookie out
of the hospital all of a sudden.

93
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:34,867
Did you see anything
written on that paper?

94
00:06:36,367 --> 00:06:41,033
No, I didn't see anything.
My mom took it from me.

95
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,133
Thanks for this again,
Auntie Astrid.

96
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,967
Do we really have
to leave this place?

97
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,300
Yes, Mom...

98
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:20,367
it will do Emma a lot of good
if we leave this place.

99
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:23,367
There's nothing here
but painful memories.

100
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,533
Why do we have
to move to Manila?

101
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,233
The rent is expensive
over there.

102
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:29,167
Everything is expensive there.

103
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:31,967
Mom, my company
re-assigned me there.

104
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:36,933
And Emma can find
a job once we get there.

105
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:42,300
Thank you for agreeing
to come with us, Mom.

106
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:45,567
I'm not gonna let you
leave me here by myself.

107
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:47,967
I can't afford
to live on my own.

108
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,067
Let me get that for you.

109
00:08:00,267 --> 00:08:02,300
- Dan?
- Yes?

110
00:08:05,133 --> 00:08:06,967
Are you sure about this?

111
00:08:07,033 --> 00:08:09,333
Are we making a good decision?

112
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,300
Do you really think
this will be good for us?

113
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,900
Emma, we need to do this.

114
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:16,300
You need this.

115
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:18,300
We have to start again.

116
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,300
I want to forget.

117
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:27,333
See, that's the answer
to your own question. Right?

118
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,967
We made the right decision.

119
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:31,533
Don't worry.

120
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:34,400
Let's go.

121
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,367
What are you doing in my office?

122
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:54,700
Why did you open my vault?

123
00:09:54,767 --> 00:10:00,100
Who gave you permission to snoop
on my things?

124
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:03,100
I just want to know
the truth, Olive.

125
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,567
Truth about what?

126
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:05,800
I didn't want to do this.

127
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:10,733
I don't want to meddle
with your private life.

128
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:15,700
But as your friend and employee,

129
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:17,200
I respect your boundaries.

130
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:20,200
But I've been hearing things

131
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:21,900
that are starting
to worry me, Olive.

132
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:25,467
About Mookie.

133
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:30,567
What about Mookie?

134
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:39,567
I know that you had her admitted
at St. Agnes Hospital.

135
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,700
How did you know about that?

136
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,700
It doesn't matter.

137
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:49,133
But this medical report proves
that Mookie is not sick.

138
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,600
That she's actually
a healthy kid.

139
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:57,433
These documents
don't mean anything.

140
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,400
This report
is from 10 years ago.

141
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,833
You said Mookie
was a sickly child.

142
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,267
If this medical report
was from ten years ago,

143
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:08,400
does that mean
that you lied before?

144
00:11:10,033 --> 00:11:14,400
Astrid, don't get
my words twisted.

145
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:18,500
I know my daughter's
medical history.

146
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,600
Why did you pull her
out of the hospital?

147
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:24,333
Because the doctors were wrong!

148
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,567
They don't want to believe
that my daughter is sick!

149
00:11:29,267 --> 00:11:30,633
Is it true, Olive?

150
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:33,567
What do you mean?

151
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:36,533
Is Mookie really sick or...

152
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,400
did you just make everything up?

153
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,600
Danilo, what's going on?
Are we there yet?

154
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:52,367
We're almost there, Mom.
There, in that next village.

155
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:53,833
There. That's where we're going.

156
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,767
Be patient.

157
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:59,833
It's too hot! And this car
of yours is so junky!

158
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:03,433
I'm all shook up.

159
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,467
What?

160
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:06,500
Oh, my.

161
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:07,900
We're almost there, Mom.

162
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:10,267
It feels like
I'm inside a blender.

163
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:11,433
What was that?

164
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:16,867
What was that?

165
00:12:16,933 --> 00:12:18,967
Sir, what are you doing,
why did you stop?

166
00:12:19,033 --> 00:12:20,267
What happened?

167
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,967
The car overheated.

168
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,033
Dan, did you bring water?

169
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:25,167
No, I didn't bring any water.

170
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:27,067
- You didn't even bring water?
- Nope.

171
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:29,433
- I'll ask for some water.
- Sir, what happened?

172
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,300
What is going on?
Don't take too long, Emma.

173
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:33,133
Okay, Mom.

174
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:58,200
- Excuse me. Can I...
- Come on, let's go.

175
00:14:58,267 --> 00:15:00,467
Oh, no, Flor. Can we stay
out a bit more?

176
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:01,567
You can't.

177
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:02,967
- You can't stay out long...
- come on.

178
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:06,000
your mom said it,
she'll get mad at me.

179
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:07,300
There, let's try it now.

180
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:15,033
There! It's good now.

181
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:16,367
It's working.

182
00:15:16,433 --> 00:15:18,167
Good!

183
00:15:18,233 --> 00:15:20,167
Emma, let's go.

184
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:23,333
The car is fixed, our house
is not far from here now.

185
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,367
Let's go.

186
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,167
Let's go.

187
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,800
What does it look like inside?

188
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:39,733
It's so big!
But it's kinda scary.

189
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,900
I don't want to live there.
Let's go.

190
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:43,400
Come on, Mom.

191
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:49,967
I'm getting goosebumps.

192
00:15:50,033 --> 00:15:52,800
- Is it fixed, are you sure?
- I'm sure, Mom.

193
00:15:52,867 --> 00:15:57,300
Oh my, what if...

194
00:15:57,367 --> 00:16:00,000
go help your wife,
you're not a gentleman.

195
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:11,133
Do you honestly believe...

196
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:16,667
that I'm making
my daughter sick?

197
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:21,033
Why on earth would I do
such a thing, Astrid?

198
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,967
I'm not sure.

199
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:27,133
Exactly.

200
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:33,800
Because you don't know
what you're talking about.

201
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:36,933
I feel like you're
doing something wrong.

202
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:48,100
You don't know
what I went through...

203
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:52,733
when I lost Angela.

204
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,833
And how Mookie filled
the emptiness I felt...

205
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,700
when I lost her.

206
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:09,000
She made me want to live,

207
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:16,267
I cherish her
with all of my life.

208
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:23,700
So tell me.

209
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:30,900
Why would I want to harm
my own daughter?

210
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:43,100
If my uncle didn't ask me
for a favor,

211
00:17:43,167 --> 00:17:46,267
I wouldn't let you live here.

212
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:50,167
No deposit,
and half the usual rent.

213
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:52,933
Where can you find
that around here?

214
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,233
Yes, I'm sorry for the trouble
Ma'am Tina.

215
00:17:56,300 --> 00:18:01,400
Don't worry, I'll pay you
the moment I get paid.

216
00:18:01,467 --> 00:18:03,933
Make sure that you will.

217
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,933
I get a lot of inquiries
from renters here.

218
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,500
I will. Thank you,
I'm sorry for the trouble.

219
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:12,800
She's acting like we're not
going to pay her rent.

220
00:18:12,867 --> 00:18:17,200
As if she's renting out
a palace.

221
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:21,300
I'm sorry about that Mom,

222
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,300
my boss helped me
get this house.

223
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:25,233
Ma'am Tina is his niece.

224
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:29,133
That's why I got this
place for a cheaper rent.

225
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:32,433
But I promise, once I get paid
and save up some money,

226
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,867
we will move to a bigger house.

227
00:18:45,867 --> 00:18:46,833
Emma,

228
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:52,367
don't tell me you're
going to talk about that again.

229
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:56,600
That you heard that lullaby
at that big house.

230
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:58,733
That's right,

231
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:01,233
perhaps you're missing
Kyla again.

232
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:04,833
I think it's better

233
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:08,767
if you use all your time
on finding a job.

234
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:10,233
You know the status
of your husband's job.

235
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,667
It's unstable.

236
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,367
No work, no pay.

237
00:19:17,033 --> 00:19:19,200
There you go again, Mom.

238
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:21,500
You're starting that again.

239
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,333
It's better that way.

240
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:27,900
It will distract you
from thinking about Kyla.

241
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,067
We're in Manila now,
we have to work harder.

242
00:19:32,133 --> 00:19:35,800
So that landlord
won't look down on us.

243
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:36,833
She's so full of herself.

244
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:39,067
Look at this cave
she called a house!

245
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:41,300
You have a point, Mom.

246
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:46,767
You're right, we moved here,
to start over.

247
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:36,067
I wish...

248
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:41,400
I'm getting hugged by her.

249
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:48,267
I wish that all moms are loving.

250
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:51,100
I wish...

251
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:54,800
my mom was like this.
